To get technical most switches in homes are single pole, single throw, where it's either an open circuit (off) or a closed circuit (on). A single pole double throw would look similar to a single throw, however the “off” position would be connected to another circuit (think if you had a backup generator and main electric coming into a house, you'd use a double throw for that so you could connect to either the main or the generator). Along with more backfeeding protection tho, but trying to not over complicate...
